</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9536D0FFA6FF95FF5B8CAE2FFF19D3" blockId="6.[136,1451,1977,2076]" lastBlockId="7.[136,1452,158,509]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="232" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA6FF94FF5B8CAE2C7C1FFB" author="Shaw, J. M. H." box="[136,325,1977,2004]" pageId="6" pageNumber="231" pagination="17 - 79" refId="ref8785" refString="Shaw, J. M. H. (2008) An investigation of the cultivated Kalanchoe daigremontiana group, with a checklist of Kalanchoe cultivars. Hanburyana 3: 17 - 79." type="journal article" year="2008">Shaw (2008: 66)</bibRefCitation>
recorded the name 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA6FF94FDF48CAD2F031FFC" box="[551,570,1978,2003]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">K</emphasis>
. ‘Pearl Bells’ for a plant with an upright habit and pendent flowers. As far as we were able to determine, this cultivar name was for the first time established by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA6FF94FBF08CCA29D81FD7" author="Shaw, J. M. H." box="[1059,1249,2013,2040]" pageId="6" pageNumber="231" pagination="17 - 79" refId="ref8785" refString="Shaw, J. M. H. (2008) An investigation of the cultivated Kalanchoe daigremontiana group, with a checklist of Kalanchoe cultivars. Hanburyana 3: 17 - 79." type="journal article" year="2008">Shaw (2008: 66)</bibRefCitation>
, with the minimal description “Upright habit, hanging flowers” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA6FF94FD4D83162EBF1034" author="Brickell, C. D. &amp; Alexander, C. &amp; Cubey, J. J. &amp; David, J. C. &amp; Hoffman, M. H. A. &amp; Leslie, A. C. &amp; Malecot, V. &amp; Xiaobai, Jin" box="[670,902,2049,2076]" pageId="6" pageNumber="231" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref7460" refString="Brickell, C. D., Alexander, C., Cubey, J. J., David, J. C., Hoffman, M. H. A., Leslie, A. C., Malecot, V. &amp; Xiaobai, Jin. (2016 [June]). International code of nomenclature for cultivated plants (ICNCP or Cultivated Plant Code), incorporating the Rules and Recommendations for naming plants in cultivation adopted by the International Union of Biological Sciences and the International Commission for the Nomenclature of Cultivated Plants. 9 th edn. International Society for Horticultural Science (ISHS), Leuven, Belgium. Scripta Horticulturae 18: 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="2016">
Brickell 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA6FF94FCD783152E001034" box="[772,825,2049,2075]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 27.2). Plants available in the horticultural trade under this name are strikingly similar to material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA7FF95FCC98B882EE71897" box="[794,990,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FCC98B882EE71897" box="[794,990,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">K. porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the species, as well as to 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FADE8B88281E1897" box="[1293,1319,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">K.</emphasis>
‘Wendy’, a supposed hybrid (see above).Although material with double flowers are occasionally sold as 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FB5C8BD4299B18F3" box="[1167,1186,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">K</emphasis>
. ‘Pearl Bells’, the name is most often applied to, and sold as, a single-flowered variety (pers. obs.). Furthermore, if this cultivar was indeed double-flowered, a trait rarely encountered in, or bred into, kalanchoes, it is likely that 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA7FF95FBB78A1D2819190A" author="Shaw, J. M. H." box="[1124,1312,266,293]" pageId="7" pageNumber="232" pagination="17 - 79" refId="ref8785" refString="Shaw, J. M. H. (2008) An investigation of the cultivated Kalanchoe daigremontiana group, with a checklist of Kalanchoe cultivars. Hanburyana 3: 17 - 79." type="journal article" year="2008">Shaw (2008: 66)</bibRefCitation>
would have mentioned it, as he had sight of the pendant flowers. Therefore, we regard this cultivar name as referring to singleflowered material that is most likely the same as or derived from 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FCAF8A442EAF1943" box="[892,918,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">K.</emphasis>
‘Wendy’. In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA7FF95FB4F8A45282C1943" authority="Pearl" authorityName=", Hamet" authorityYear="1907" box="[1180,1301,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FB4F8A45282C1943" box="[1180,1301,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
‘Pearl Bells’ is in all respects virtually indistinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA7FF95FD628A602E4C19BF" box="[689,885,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FD628A602E4C19BF" box="[689,885,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">K. porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Even though use of 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FBB58A60294019BF" box="[1126,1145,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">K</emphasis>
. ‘Pearl Bells’ is acceptable under 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA7FF95FF1D8A8D2C8B199B" author="Brickell, C. D. &amp; Alexander, C. &amp; Cubey, J. J. &amp; David, J. C. &amp; Hoffman, M. H. A. &amp; Leslie, A. C. &amp; Malecot, V. &amp; Xiaobai, Jin" box="[206,434,410,437]" pageId="7" pageNumber="232" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref7460" refString="Brickell, C. D., Alexander, C., Cubey, J. J., David, J. C., Hoffman, M. H. A., Leslie, A. C., Malecot, V. &amp; Xiaobai, Jin. (2016 [June]). International code of nomenclature for cultivated plants (ICNCP or Cultivated Plant Code), incorporating the Rules and Recommendations for naming plants in cultivation adopted by the International Union of Biological Sciences and the International Commission for the Nomenclature of Cultivated Plants. 9 th edn. International Society for Horticultural Science (ISHS), Leuven, Belgium. Scripta Horticulturae 18: 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="2016">
Brickell 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FEFC8A8C2C59199B" box="[303,352,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">et al</emphasis>
. (2016
</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 21.2) as a minimum requirement, i.e., with reference to the genus name only, it is here proposed that this cultivar, with retention of the cultivar name, is to be associated with the species, as 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA7FF95FB3A8AA82DF219D3" authority="' Pearl" authorityName="Pearl" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FB3A8AA8289219F7" box="[1257,1451,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">K. porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
‘Pearl
</taxonomicName>
Bells’ (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA7FF95FEF28AF52CC619D3" author="Brickell, C. D. &amp; Alexander, C. &amp; Cubey, J. J. &amp; David, J. C. &amp; Hoffman, M. H. A. &amp; Leslie, A. C. &amp; Malecot, V. &amp; Xiaobai, Jin" box="[289,511,482,509]" pageId="7" pageNumber="232" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref7460" refString="Brickell, C. D., Alexander, C., Cubey, J. J., David, J. C., Hoffman, M. H. A., Leslie, A. C., Malecot, V. &amp; Xiaobai, Jin. (2016 [June]). International code of nomenclature for cultivated plants (ICNCP or Cultivated Plant Code), incorporating the Rules and Recommendations for naming plants in cultivation adopted by the International Union of Biological Sciences and the International Commission for the Nomenclature of Cultivated Plants. 9 th edn. International Society for Horticultural Science (ISHS), Leuven, Belgium. Scripta Horticulturae 18: 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="2016">
Brickell 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA7FF95FE578AF42C8C19D3" box="[388,437,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="232">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
: Arts 2 and 14.1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
